<TEXT>
about 50 members of a roman catholic parish held 
a mass outside their shuttered church while cars and trucks whizzed 
by but a spokesman for their archdiocese said their ceremony was 
just a stunt 
they locked us out said sandy simun a member of mother of 
our saviour church in northwest detroit for 14 years we need our 
church 
mother of our saviour was one of 30 detroit parishes with 
dwindling congregations that were ordered closed by cardinal edmund 
szoka to save money the move sparked hot criticism from some 
catholics who argued that it was discriminatory to close 
innercity churches the churches were told to close by june 30 and 
some have already done so 
mother of our saviour had 57 member families 
some members of mother of our saviour gathered sunday to protest 
the action with a service led by the rev arthur lovely from sts 
peter and paul church 
there should not have been a mass there said jay berman a 
spokesman for the 15millionmember archdiocese of detroit that 
parish has a pastor and administrator who determined that there 
would be no further sacramental activity 
its regrettable that another priest decided to come and say 
mass there 
berman declined to say if any action would be taken against 
lovely he called the service a stunt to gain media attention for 
protesters of szokas decision earlier this year to close the 
parishes 
among those attending the service was sister beth rindler who 
was fired as a pastoral associate at the church last week for 
refusing to turn over to the archdiocese 7000 contributed by 
church members she said the money belongs to the parish and not 
the archdiocese 
we do not have a situation as sister has made out where the 
money belongs to the people berman said it goes into the 
custody of the pastor and to a much smaller part the bishop to 
use in the works of the church the whole church 
simun 59 said he was willing to fight 
theyve raped us of our church and now theyre trying to rob 
us of our money simun said i have a right to revolt it hurts 
so deep 
were going to have church out here till they jail us 
since the closings plan was announced szokas residence has 
been picketed by protesters 
church officials said the closings were needed because the 
citys roman catholic population has fallen from 100000 to fewer 
than 50000 
an additional 25 churches have been given until next year to 
prove their viability 
