the big cheese is back 
the belle of wisconsin a mammoth 20ton block of cheddar 
cheese has returned home after a yearlong tour of the united 
states 
the cheese measuring 20 feet long 6 feet wide and 6 feet tall 
and weighing 40060 pounds arrived in milwaukee this weekend 
after touring 350 cities in 36 states 
in the metropolitan areas they didnt care much for it there 
was so much else going on said pat patterson 59 who drove the 
belles custommade semitrailer truck some 55000 miles in the 
last year 
but in the outlying areas and in the suburbs there was a real 
good reaction especially among the children he said some of 
them asked questions like how much milk did it take or how many 
cows did it take 
the belle will begin a second tour of wisconsin later this week 
that will end at the state fair in august the block will then be 
sliced into onepound chunks and sold around the country 
created by cheesemaker dave simon of little chute in march 
1988 and sponsored by the wisconsin milk marketing board the belle 
was marketed as the largest block of cheese ever 
wisconsin is the no 1 cheese producer in the country with an 
annual output of more than 19 billion pounds 
