<TEXT>
here are some key dates in the nato 
alliance 
april 4 1949 nato treaty is signed in washington by 12 
countries 
feb 18 1952 greece and turkey join nato 
may 5 1955 west germany joins nato 
aug 13 1961 berlin wall constructed 
nov 20 1962 soviets agree to remove missile bases from cuba 
june 20 1963 washington and moscow agree on a hotline 
march 10 1966 france leaves natos integrated military 
structure 
oct 16 1967 nato headquarters moves from paris to brussels 
aug 2021 1968 soviet polish east german bulgarian and 
hungarian troops invade czechoslovakia 
may 26 1972 interim agreement on strategic arms limitations 
salt i signed in moscow 
oct 30 1973 mutual and balanced force reduction talks on 
troop cuts in central europe begin in vienna 
june 18 1979 strategic arms limitation agreement salt ii 
signed in vienna by president carter and soviet leader leonid 
brezhnev 
dec 12 1979 nato agrees on twintrack decision to deploy 
cruise and pershing 2 nuclear missiles in europe but seeks talks on 
reducing these intermediaterange nuclear forces in europe 
nov 30 1981 the united states and the soviet union open 
talks in geneva on reducing intermediaterange nuclear forces or 
inf 
may 30 1982 spain becomes the 16th member of nato 
december 1983 inf deployment begins in britain west germany 
and italy 
dec 8 1987 president reagan and soviet leader mikhail 
gorbachev sign the inf treaty in washington 
march 9 1989 nato and the warsaw pact nations open talks in 
vienna on reducing conventional arms in an area from the atlantic 
ocean to the ural mountains 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

