<TEXT>
anatoly i lukyanov was virtually unknown to the 
country when he was confirmed monday as vice president to his old 
law school classmate mikhail s gorbachev 
the televised questioning of lukyanov by deputies in the soviet 
parliament gave millions their first glimpse of the trim 
bespectacled legal specialist who has worked his whole life in the 
state and communist party apparatus 
lukyanov 59 emerged from the process as a man adept at the 
ageold political skill of evading piercing questions and as could 
be expected a loyal supporter of gorbachev who was once his 
deputy 
historian roy a medvedev disclosed during the questioning that 
in the early 1950s lukyanov was chairman of a party youth 
committee at moscow state university when gorbachev was its vice 
chairman both were studying law at the university 
lukyanov fielded dozens of questions from members of the 
congress of peoples deputies ranging from his attitude toward the 
rising crime rate to the 1939 sovietgerman pact that led to the 
forced incorporation of the baltic republics into the soviet union 
tamaz v gamkrelidze of the southern republic of georgia 
demanded to know lukyanovs exact role in events that led antiriot 
forces to move against proindependence demonstrators in tbilisi on 
april 9 resulting in at least 20 deaths 
as with most other questions lukyanov carefully sidestepped a 
direct answer pointing to ongoing investigations of the events 
medvedev questioned whether lukyanov will pursue gorbachevs 
policies faithfully when gorbachev is abroad or on vacation 
policy sometimes changes 50 60 or even 180 degrees medvedev 
said 
lukyanov replied with general statements of support for 
gorbachevs efforts to democratize the soviet union and remove the 
stalinist abuses of the past 
western analysts assume the old ties and similarities between 
the two prompted gorbachev last fall to pluck lukyanov from the 
obscurity of the bureaucracy to make him a candidate member of the 
partys ruling politburo and vice president of the supreme soviet 
the old parliament 
on monday under the restructured political system that permits 
gorbachev to pick his own vice president subject to confirmation 
by the congress he won overwhelming backing as first deputy of the 
chairman of the supreme soviet or more simply vicepresident 
according to constitutional reforms approved last year the 
first deputy and a yettobedetermined number of deputies to 
gorbachev can fulfill certain of the presidents functions if 
gorbachev authorizes them to do so 
they also are entitled to replace gorbachev in the case of his 
absence or if he is incapable of performing his duties the 
constitution does not specifically make lukyanov gorbachevs 
successor in such event 
little is known about lukyanovs early career he was born may 
7 1930 in smolensk and began work at 13 in a world war ii 
munitions factory in the saratov region on the volga river in 
southern russia 
joining the communist party in 1955 lukyanov went to work as a 
government legal consultant after completing his legal studies in 
1956 
in that capacity he helped reach agreements on soviet 
assistance to poland and hungary in 1956 when both countries saw 
uprisings against stalinist rule 
in 1985 when gorbachev became party chief lukyanov was named 
to head the party central committees general department which 
handles domestic affairs in 1987 he rose to become central 
committee secretary for politburo staff work and supervision of the 
military security intelligence and legal institutions 
lukyanov is known to have visited denmark in 1986 and yugoslavia 
in 1987 but his answer to a question on his role in czechoslovakia 
after the sovietled warsaw pact invasion of 1968 suggested he was 
among the many of us who went out to help czechoslovakias 
communist party and youth organizations after the invasion 
it is not known whether lukyanov an ethnic russian is married 
or has children 
