received the largest popular vote of any candidate when he won a 
seat on the congress in march on saturday the congress chose from 
among its members to form the supreme soviet 
through a quirk in the election procedure yeltsin the former 
moscow party boss and populist candidate finished last on a list 
of 12 candidates for 11 russian federation seats in one of the two 
chambers of the supreme soviet 
he was therefore defeated despite his having received more than 
50 percent of the votes cast by his fellow deputies 
after yeltsin and other prominent reformminded deputies were 
