after he left the congress wellwishers hung from trees and tossed 
red roses 
yeltsin smiling broadly led a spontaneous onehour march from 
the kremlin along gorky street to pushkin square where about 5000 
people gathered women kissed him and men shook his hand 
all the people are with you one man yelled 
yeltsin thanked the throng through a megaphone and ended the 
rally with hands held high in a gesture of victory 
also on monday gorbachev pushed his choice for vice president 
anatoly i lukyanov through the congress but not before the 
deputies subjected the littleknown schoolmate of gorbachevs to 
tough questioning on his views and fitness for the job 
the 2250seat congress empowered to elect the national 
president from among its own members and to confirm the presidents 
choice of vice president let omsk university law professor alexei 
i kazannik vacate his spot in the bicameral supreme soviet in 
order to have yeltsin take his place 
the decision reached in minutes without a direct vote on 
yeltsins candidacy defused a tense situation that developed when 
the outspoken opponent of official privilege finished last on a 
