1930 gen gen francisco gassino the army chief of staff said in 
a speech to soldiers monday we are not disposed to repeat 
errors although the gravity of the situation troubles our 
spirits 
since february the austral currency has lost more than 90 
percent of its value against the dollar inflation this month alone 
may exceed 70 percent which would be an annual rate of 58162 
percent 
a central bank announcement said earlier monday banks and 
foreign exchange houses that were closed or restricted may 22 would 
resume normal operations tuesday 
alfonsin sent congress tax and spending measures aimed at 
stabilizing the economy other measures he mentioned in a 
nationwide address sunday night took effect by decree including 
free subway passes for students and senior citizens 
he pledged to reduce the budget deficit by cutting spending on 
capital projects increasing export taxes and enforcing income tax 
laws raising fees for public services and selling stateowned 
radio and television stations 
he also promised to enforce price guidelines 
real wages have fallen by 30 percent since january according to 
the latin america research foundation and are at the lowest level 
since alfonsin took office in december 1983 
