<TEXT>
when president bush 
sails by the towering lorelei rock wednesday he will see one of 
the most enduring symbols of romantic germany but with an american 
flag snapping atop the craggy peak 
legend has it that when rhine river boatsmen sailed by the rock 
in days of old a shimmering goldenhaired maiden lured them into 
shipwreck and death with her mesmerizing songs 
this is certainly the prettiest part of the rhine says rolf 
daum mayor of the town that includes the lorelei weve had 
several presidents and heads of state sail past over the years 
the sightseeing cruise aboard the tripledecked stolzenfels was 
planned as the final event of bushs twoday trip to west germany 
bush was being accompanied by west german chancellor helmut kohl 
and 300 invited guests 
daum says the riverfront town of st goarhausen will be 
decorated in a sea of flags and local townsfolk will be waving 
people here are very proud of this he said 
ute port 24 a local pharmacists assistant voted this years 
weinhexe received the honor of seeing bush off weinhexe 
literally means wine witch and the young womans duties 
include promoting the local brands at festivals and similar events 
the itinerary called for the presidential party to head north 
from oberwesel where the 1000year auf schoenburg castle looms 
above the river to the ancient city of koblenz 
security boats will be shielding the presidential cruise from 
the barges from belgium the netherlands france switzerland and 
west germany that ply the rhine daily 
the river has spawned many legends including one that 19th 
century german composer richard wagner turned into his cycle of 
operas called the ring of the nibelungs 
the legend of the lorelei the beautiful siren singing from the 
rock high above the river bank was immortalized by german poet 
heinrich heine 
heines poem ends 
i believe the waves swallow up 
the boatsman and his boat in the end 
and thats what with her song 
the lorelei has done 
among the other sites along the route 
the burg katz or cat castle in a sign that change comes to 
the most traditionbound areas the west german government is 
negotiating to sell the castle to a japanese businessman who wants 
to turn it into a luxury hotel other rhine castles have been 
converted into hotels and restaurants 
burg maus or mouse castle another towering fortress that 
according to legend sparked a local noble family to build the burg 
katz out of jealousy 
ruins of the sterrenberg and liebenstein castles built next to 
each other by two brothers locked in a legendary rivalry 
the storybook town of boppard 
im disappointed he couldnt stop here mayor wolfgang gipp 
said but the president cant be everywhere 
the marksburg castle a conglomeration of spires and 
chateaustyle buildings high atop a steep treecovered hill the 
marksburg is the only rhine castle that was never destroyed 
the last major castle is the stolzenfels a sprawling complex 
that also gave the name to the presidential cruise ship 
the cruise ends in koblenz a city that dates to roman times and 
where the mosel river flows into the rhine 
city spokeswoman dorothee steinhoppe said that after his 
arrival bush will visit the enormous pedestal of a nowdestroyed 
monument to kaiser wilhelm i who united germany in 1871 
american artillery destroyed the monument during world war 
ii ms steinhoppe said adding that bushs visit is the first 
by an american president to the city 
local officials planned to give bush a silver tray engraved with 
thanks for the fond memory of his visit to the city 
